 "faq": [
  {
   "question": "Where does Protection Warrior Phase 2 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 251 top-ranked Protection Warrior DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 2 (Serpentshrine Cavern and Tempest Keep), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Protection Warrior items in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Dragonstrike (65%), Serpentshrine Shuriken (64%), Veteran's Plate Greaves (59%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Serpentshrine Cavern and Tempest Keep."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Protection Warrior use in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Relentless Earthstorm Diamond in the meta socket, then Solid Star of Elune and Glinting Noble Topaz in the coloured sockets. Epic gems only arrive with patch 2.4 (Sunwell), so these rare-quality cuts are the ceiling for this phase."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Protection Warrior need in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "11 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of the Defender on head, Greater Inscription of the Knight on shoulders, Nethercleft Leg Armor on legs and Enchant Weapon - Crusader on main hand. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of the Defender comes from Alurmi — Caverns of Time."
  }
 ]
